  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> rice noodles </strong>to a bowl and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Set aside for 12-15 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, drain the noodles, reserving 150ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [225ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[300ml]</span> <strong>starchy noodle water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678880530461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678880530461-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678880530461-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678880530461-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1678880530461-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, tear your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> torn mushrooms</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until golden brown all over</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678880535802-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678880535802-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678880535802-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678880535802-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1678880535802-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mushrooms are cooking, chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> in half</p><p>Top, tail, and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal (peeling is optional)</p><p>Slice each individual <strong>carrot disc</strong> into matchsticks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678880546673-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678880546673-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678880546673-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678880546673-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1678880546673-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely, keeping the whites and greens separate</p><p>Crush your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Tip: If you don't have a rolling pin, just chop them roughly!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678880551720-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678880551720-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678880551720-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678880551720-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1678880551720-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms are golden brown, add the<strong> halved Tenderstem</strong> and <strong>carrot matchsticks </strong>to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 3-4 min or until the broccoli is almost tender</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678880561307-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678880561307-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678880561307-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678880561307-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1678880561307-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, combine your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>cornflour</strong> in a measuring jug</p><p>Gradually stir in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]<strong> </span>starchy noodle water</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>tamari</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) – this is your<strong> tamari stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678880566827-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678880566827-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678880566827-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678880566827-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1678880566827-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the broccoli is almost tender, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>spring onion whites</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tamari stock</strong> with a pinch of<strong> pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until it begins to thicken, then add the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice noodles</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for a final 1-2 min or until the sauce is thick and coating the noodles – this is your<strong> mushroom pad see ew-style noodles</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678880574118-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678880574118-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678880574118-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678880574118-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1678880574118-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> mushroom pad see ew-style noodles</strong> topped with the <strong>spring onion greens </strong>and <strong>crushed peanuts</strong></p><p>Drizzle your <strong>sriracha</strong> over the top (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
